{"favorite_id": 10145, "calc_type": "", "dosing": false, "full_title_en": "Rapid Emergency Medicine Score (REMS)", "short_title_en": "REMS", "medium_description_en": "Predicts in-hospital mortality in nonsurgical adult patients presenting to the ED.", "short_description_en": "In-hospital mortality in emergency patients.", "before_use": "", "instructions_en": "", "purpose_en": ["Prognosis"], "disease_en": ["Trauma"], "specialty_en": ["Critical Care", "Emergency Medicine", "Hospitalist Medicine", "Internal Medicine"], "chief_complaint_en": ["Injury/Trauma"], "system_en": ["Any/All"], "search_abbreviation_en": ["Raps", "rapid", "acute", "physiology", "score", "emergency department", "rems", "hospital mortality"], "slug": "rapid-emergency-medicine-score-rems", "seo": {"meta_description_en": "The Rapid Emergency Medicine Score (REMS) predicts in-hospital mortality in nonsurgical patients presenting to the ED.", "keywords_en": "Raps, rapid, acute, physiology, score, emergency department"}, "content": {"how_to_use": {"use_case_en": "<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-28f6fb14-7fff-72a9-da93-680dbd23c77d\"></p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Critically ill patients, where in-hospital mortality prediction may help guide treatment modalities.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Not validated for pediatric patients.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>", "pearls_pitfalls_en": "<p>Not validated for pediatric patients.</p>", "why_use_en": "<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-1154c9b7-7fff-a1af-c4f2-2c1d74751e21\"></p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">May not add to clinician gestalt, but can be useful in the prehospital setting for determining whether a patient would benefit from rapid access to advanced life support services.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Superior (<a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15078500\" target=\"_blank\">Olsson 2004</a>)&nbsp;to the Rapid Acute Physiology Score (RAPS) (<a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/3593492\" target=\"_blank\">Rhee 1987</a>) and non-inferior to <calculator id=\"1868\">APACHE II</calculator> (<a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/14525735\" target=\"_blank\">Olsson 2003</a>).</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Calculated with values obtained out of hospital, or in hospital without lab studies.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Helps guide aggressiveness of treatment with parameters routinely acquired in the prehospital setting.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}, "next_steps": {"advice_en": "<p dir=\"ltr\">High&nbsp;risk&nbsp;(REMS &ge;3): patient may need aggressive treatment.</p>\n<p>Low risk (REMS &lt;3): patient may be appropriate to triage for routine treatment (in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15078500\" target=\"_blank\">Olsson 2004</a>, all patients with REMS &lt;3 survived).<br /><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-e508ac34-7fff-0dc8-a00a-fc54f9bff820\"></p>", "management_en": "<ul>\n<li><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-d87ade1e-7fff-310d-b040-787736ad0c95\">Mortality rapidly increases above a score of 10. Consider more aggressive treatment in patients with higher scores (in conjunction with patient wishes and clinical judgment).</li>\n<li>Clinical judgment of a patient&rsquo;s presentation should always be used to determine need for advanced interventions.</li>\n</ul>", "critical_actions_en": ""}, "about": {"formula_en": "<p dir=\"ltr\">Addition of the selected points:</p>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<table><colgroup><col width=\"200\" /><col width=\"136\" /><col width=\"113\" /></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Variable</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Points</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"5\">Age, years</td>\n<td>\n<p>&lt;45</p>\n</td>\n<td>0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>45-54</p>\n</td>\n<td>2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>55-64</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">3</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>65-74</p>\n</td>\n<td>5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>&gt;74</p>\n</td>\n<td>6